  "text": "The calculations of the line shape parameters, the half-width and line (pressure)-shift coefficients, were made using the complex formalism of Robert and Bonamy [CITATION_1] as modified by Ma et al. [CITATION_2] and is labeled as the Modified Complex Robert-Bonamy (MCRB) formulation. The half-width, c, and line shift, d, of a ro-vibrational transition f i are given by real and imaginary parts of the complex valued expression: ). f Temperature dependence exponent of line mixing (unitless) determined to be 0.69 [CITATION_3] for this air-broadened pair of transitions only. In all other cases the temperature dependence exponent of line mixing was fixed to 0.70.",
